Description: Fragment of double handle at neck join from a Koan pottery transport amphora. Clay fine orange-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with club symbol and Greek inscription.
Findspot: Found/Acquired: Naukratis, Possibly Site 28 (Petrie) [based on pencil mark] (?)
Curator's comments: Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.163, 23 or 181,30. Name, Minnio. Pencil '28'.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0188)
